    "So, reliable (i.e.",
    "pervasive) coupling is often precisely what is thought to be required for constitution -at least where there is some prior agreement of the nature of the phenomenon that the causally integrated elements constitute.",
    "Since this agreement is just what the debate around HEC lacks, however, Adams and Aizawa's challenge and the responses elicited by it have led to an impasse.",
    "Theorists on one side of the argument emphasise continuities, and on the other dissimilarities, between information processing inside and outside the head, claiming these differences as the basis for allowing or disallowing extended processes under the rubric of cognition (for overviews, see Aizawa, 2017; Gallagher, 2018; Facchin, 2023).",
    "Connecting to the discussion of norms and teleology in (§2.1), I want to lay out an action theoretic way forward."
